        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 8:43AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 842 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arroyo City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beach Access Five, Beach Access Four, Arroyo City, South Padre Island
Convention Center, Las Yescas Elementary School, Beach Access Six, La
Tina, Las Yescas, South Padre Island Birding Center, and Monte
Grande.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
